## üí∞ **Explore the Azure Pricing Calculator**

*(Completed ‚Äì 100 XP ‚Äì 2 minutes)*

---

### üß≠ **What is the Azure Pricing Calculator?**

The **Azure Pricing Calculator** is a **free online tool** that helps estimate the cost of Azure services **before** you deploy them.
It lets you explore different resource configurations and understand potential monthly costs.

üîó **Website:** [https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/pricing/calculator](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/pricing/calculator)

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è **Purpose**

* To **estimate costs** for different Azure services (Compute, Storage, Databases, Networking, etc.)
* To **compare regions, configurations, and pricing tiers**
* To **plan budgets** before deployment
* To **customize scenarios** for multiple services in one estimate

---

### üß© **Key Features**

| Feature                   | Description                                                                         |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Add Services**          | Add Azure services like VMs, SQL Databases, Storage Accounts, etc. to your estimate |
| **Region Selection**      | Choose Azure regions (prices vary by region)                                        |
| **Configuration Options** | Modify VM size, OS, storage redundancy, access tier, etc.                           |
| **Cost Breakdown**        | View hourly, monthly, or annual cost estimates                                      |
| **Export & Share**        | Save or export the pricing estimate to Excel for planning                           |
| **Currency Selection**    | View costs in your preferred local currency                                         |
| **Support Plans**         | Include Azure support pricing if needed                                             |

---

### üßÆ **Example Use Case**

| Step | Example                                                                              |
| ---- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| 1Ô∏è‚É£  | Go to the **Azure Pricing Calculator** website                                       |
| 2Ô∏è‚É£  | Click **+ Add Products**                                                             |
| 3Ô∏è‚É£  | Choose **Virtual Machine**                                                           |
| 4Ô∏è‚É£  | Select **Region: Central India**, **VM size: D2s_v3**, **OS: Windows**               |
| 5Ô∏è‚É£  | Choose **1-year Reserved Instance** for savings                                      |
| 6Ô∏è‚É£  | The calculator displays an **estimated monthly cost** for the VM                     |
| 7Ô∏è‚É£  | Add additional resources like **Storage** or **Network Bandwidth** to see total cost |

---

### üí° **Important Notes**

* The calculator is for **estimation only** ‚Äî it doesn‚Äôt create or charge for any resources.
* The **Total Cost of Ownership (TCO)** calculator is now **retired**.
* You can use it to estimate **end-to-end workload costs** before deployment.

---

### üìä **Benefits**

| Benefit             | Explanation                                                |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Transparency**    | Know the cost before deploying any resource                |
| **Customization**   | Adjust parameters and instantly see impact on cost         |
| **Comparison**      | Evaluate cost differences across regions or configurations |
| **Budget Planning** | Helps forecast operational expenses for your organization  |

